                                <p>Regular lettering with short serifs at the end of some letter strokes (epsilon, sigma, tau, upsilon, omega): alpha has a straight crossbar, pi a shorter right vertical and projecting top bar; sigma has parallel, mu parallel and slightly diverging outer strokes; round letters are for the most part almost full size: theta has a central point; omega has prominant finials, and phi an extended stem.</p>
